#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:118
msgid "Managing connections"
msgstr "管理连接"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:120
msgid ""
"Some games accept connections at any time, others during the lobby phase. "
"Godot can be requested to no longer accept connections at any point (see "
"``set_refuse_new_network_connections(bool)`` and related methods on :ref:"
"`SceneTree <class_SceneTree>`). To manage who connects, Godot provides the "
"following signals in SceneTree:"
msgstr ""
"有些游戏可以随时接受连接，而其他游戏则可以在大厅阶段接受。可以要求Godot在任何"
"时候都不再接受连接（请参阅 ``set_refuse_new_network_connections(bool)`` 和"
"在 :ref:`SceneTree <class_SceneTree>` 上的相关方法）。为了管理连接的对象，"
"Godot在 ``SceneTree`` 中提供了以下信号："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:123
msgid "Server and Clients:"
msgstr "服务器和客户端："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:125
msgid "``network_peer_connected(int id)``"
msgstr "``network_peer_connected(int id)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:126
msgid "``network_peer_disconnected(int id)``"
msgstr "``network_peer_disconnected(int id)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:128
msgid ""
"The above signals are called on every peer connected to the server "
"(including on the server) when a new peer connects or disconnects. Clients "
"will connect with a unique ID greater than 1, while network peer ID 1 is "
"always the server. Anything below 1 should be handled as invalid. You can "
"retrieve the ID for the local system via :ref:`SceneTree."
"get_network_unique_id() <class_SceneTree_method_get_network_unique_id>`. "
"These IDs will be useful mostly for lobby management and should generally be "
"stored, as they identify connected peers and thus players. You can also use "
"IDs to send messages only to certain peers."
msgstr ""
"当新的对等体连接或断开连接时，在连接到服务器的每个对等体（包括服务器上）上都"
"会调用上述信号。客户端将使用大于1的唯一ID连接，而网络对等ID 1始终是服务器。 "
"低于1的任何内容都应视为无效。您可以通过 :ref:`SceneTree."
"get_network_unique_id() <class_SceneTree_method_get_network_unique_id>` 检索"
"本地系统的ID。这些ID主要用于大厅管理，通常应存储起来，因为它们标识了已连接的"
"同伴并因此确定了玩家。您还可以使用ID仅将消息发送给某些对等体。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:134
msgid "Clients:"
msgstr "客户端："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:136
msgid "``connected_to_server``"
msgstr "``connected_to_server``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:137
msgid "``connection_failed``"
msgstr "``connection_failed``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:138
msgid "``server_disconnected``"
msgstr "``server_disconnected``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:140
msgid ""
"Again, all these functions are mainly useful for lobby management or for "
"adding/removing players on the fly. For these tasks, the server clearly has "
"to work as a server and you have to perform tasks manually such as sending a "
"newly connected player information about other already connected players (e."
"g. their names, stats, etc)."
msgstr ""
"同样，所有这些函数主要用于大厅管理或即时添加/删除玩家。对于这些任务，服务器显"
"然必须作为服务器工作，并且您必须手动执行任务，例如向一个新连接的游戏角色发送"
"其他已经连接游戏角色的信息（例如，他们的姓名，状态等）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:144
msgid ""
"Lobbies can be implemented any way you want, but the most common way is to "
"use a node with the same name across scenes in all peers. Generally, an "
"autoloaded node/singleton is a great fit for this, to always have access to, "
"e.g. \"/root/lobby\"."
msgstr ""
"可以按照您想要的任何方式来实现大厅，但是最常见的方法是在所有对等体的场景之"
"间，使用具有一个相同名称的节点。通常，一个自动加载的节点/单例非常适合此操作，"
"以便可以在任何时候访问它，例如 ``/root/lobby``。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:148
msgid "RPC"
msgstr "RPC"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:150
msgid ""
"To communicate between peers, the easiest way is to use RPCs (remote "
"procedure calls). This is implemented as a set of functions in :ref:`Node "
"<class_Node>`:"
msgstr ""
"为了在对等体之间进行通信，最简单的方法是使用RPC（远程过程调用）。这是作为 :"
"ref:`Node <class_Node>` 中的一组函数实现的："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:153
msgid "``rpc(\"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"
msgstr "``rpc(\"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:154
msgid "``rpc_id(<peer_id>,\"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"
msgstr "``rpc_id(<peer_id>,\"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:155
msgid "``rpc_unreliable(\"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"
msgstr "``rpc_unreliable(\"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:156
msgid "``rpc_unreliable_id(<peer_id>, \"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"
msgstr "``rpc_unreliable_id(<peer_id>, \"function_name\", <optional_args>)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:158
msgid "Synchronizing member variables is also possible:"
msgstr "也可以同步成员变量："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:160
msgid "``rset(\"variable\", value)``"
msgstr "``rset(\"variable\", value)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:161
msgid "``rset_id(<peer_id>, \"variable\", value)``"
msgstr "``rset_id(<peer_id>, \"variable\", value)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:162
msgid "``rset_unreliable(\"variable\", value)``"
msgstr "``rset_unreliable(\"variable\", value)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:163
msgid "``rset_unreliable_id(<peer_id>, \"variable\", value)``"
msgstr "``rset_unreliable_id(<peer_id>, \"variable\", value)``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:165
msgid "Functions can be called in two fashions:"
msgstr "可以用两种方式来调用函数："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:167
msgid ""
"Reliable: the function call will arrive no matter what, but may take longer "
"because it will be re-transmitted in case of failure."
msgstr ""
"可靠：无论如何，函数调用都会到达，但是可能会花费更长的时间，因为在失败的情况"
"下它将重新传输。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:168
msgid ""
"Unreliable: if the function call does not arrive, it will not be re-"
"transmitted; but if it arrives, it will do it quickly."
msgstr ""
"不可靠：如果函数调用未到达，则不会重新传输；但是如果到达，它将很快完成。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:170
msgid ""
"In most cases, reliable is desired. Unreliable is mostly useful when "
"synchronizing object positions (sync must happen constantly, and if a packet "
"is lost, it's not that bad because a new one will eventually arrive and it "
"would likely be outdated because the object moved further in the meantime, "
"even if it was resent reliably)."
msgstr ""
"在大多数情况下，需要可靠的调用。当同步对象位置时，不可靠的调用通常很有用（同"
"步必须不断发生，并且如果丢失了一个数据包，那还不算太坏，因为一个新的数据包最"
"终会到达，并且由于对象在此期间进一步移动而可能已经过时了，即使它被可靠地重新"
"发送）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:173
msgid ""
"There is also the ``get_rpc_sender_id`` function in ``SceneTree``, which can "
"be used to check which peer (or peer ID) sent an RPC."
msgstr ""
"``SceneTree`` 中还有 ``get_rpc_sender_id`` 函数，可用于检查哪个对等体（或对等"
"体ID）发送了RPC。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:176
msgid "Back to lobby"
msgstr "回到大厅"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:178
msgid ""
"Let's get back to the lobby. Imagine that each player that connects to the "
"server will tell everyone about it."
msgstr ""
"让我们回到大厅。想象一下，连接到服务器的每个游戏角色都会将他的到来告诉其他每"
"一个人。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:224
msgid ""
"You might have already noticed something different, which is the usage of "
"the ``remote`` keyword on the ``register_player`` function:"
msgstr ""
"您可能已经注意到一些不同，即 ``register_player`` 函数中使用 ``remote`` 关键字"
"的用法："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:230
msgid ""
"This keyword has two main uses. The first is to let Godot know that this "
"function can be called from RPC. If no keywords are added, Godot will block "
"any attempts to call functions for security. This makes security work a lot "
"easier (so a client can't call a function to delete a file on another "
"client's system)."
msgstr ""
"此关键字有两个主要用途。首先是让Godot知道可以从RPC调用此函数。如果未添加任何"
"关键字，Godot将为安全性阻止任何调用函数的尝试。这使安全性工作变得容易得多（因"
"此客户端无法调用函数来删除另一个客户端系统上的文件）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:234
msgid ""
"The second use is to specify how the function will be called via RPC. There "
"are four different keywords:"
msgstr "第二个用途是指定如何通过RPC调用该函数。有四个不同的关键字："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:236
msgid "``remote``"
msgstr "``remote``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:237
msgid "``remotesync``"
msgstr "``remotesync``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:238
msgid "``master``"
msgstr "``master``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:239
msgid "``puppet``"
msgstr "``puppet``"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:241
msgid ""
"The ``remote`` keyword means that the ``rpc()`` call will go via network and "
"execute remotely."
msgstr "``remote`` 关键字意味着 ``rpc()`` 调用将通过网络发送并远程执行。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:243
msgid ""
"The ``remotesync`` keyword means that the ``rpc()`` call will go via network "
"and execute remotely, but will also execute locally (do a normal function "
"call)."
msgstr ""
"``remotesync`` 关键字意味着 ``rpc()`` 调用将通过网络发送并远程执行，但也将在"
"本地执行（执行一次普通函数调用）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:245
msgid ""
"The others will be explained further down. Note that you could also use the "
"``get_rpc_sender_id`` function on ``SceneTree`` to check which peer actually "
"made the RPC call to ``register_player``."
msgstr ""
"其他关键字将在下面进一步解释。请注意，您还可以在 ``SceneTree`` 上使用 "
"``get_rpc_sender_id`` 函数，来检查哪个对等体实际上对 ``register_player`` 进行"
"了RPC调用。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:248
msgid ""
"With this, lobby management should be more or less explained. Once you have "
"your game going, you will most likely want to add some extra security to "
"make sure clients don't do anything funny (just validate the info they send "
"from time to time, or before game start). For the sake of simplicity and "
"because each game will share different information, this is not shown here."
msgstr ""
"这样，应该或多或少地解释大厅管理。游戏开始后，您很可能希望添加一些额外的安全"
"性，以确保客户不会做任何有趣的事情（只需验证他们不时或在游戏开始之前发送的信"
"息）。为简单起见，由于每个游戏将共享不同的信息，因此此处未显示。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:253
msgid "Starting the game"
msgstr "开始游戏"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:255
msgid ""
"Once enough players have gathered in the lobby, the server should probably "
"start the game. This is nothing special in itself, but we'll explain a few "
"nice tricks that can be done at this point to make your life much easier."
msgstr ""
"一旦足够的玩家聚集在大厅中，服务器就应该开始游戏。本身并没有什么特别的，但是"
"我们将在此介绍一些不错的技巧，使您的生活更加轻松。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:259
msgid "Player scenes"
msgstr "游戏角色场景"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:261
msgid ""
"In most games, each player will likely have its own scene. Remember that "
"this is a multiplayer game, so in every peer you need to instance **one "
"scene for each player connected to it**. For a 4 player game, each peer "
"needs to instance 4 player nodes."
msgstr ""
"在大多数游戏中，每个游戏角色都可能有自己的场景。请记住，这是一款多人游戏，因"
"此在每个对等体中，您都需要实例化 **一个与之相连的每个游戏角色场景**。对于4人"
"游戏，每个对等体都需要实例化4个游戏角色节点。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:264
msgid ""
"So, how to name such nodes? In Godot, nodes need to have a unique name. It "
"must also be relatively easy for a player to tell which node represents each "
"player ID."
msgstr ""
"那么，如何命名此类节点？在Godot中，节点需要具有唯一的名称。游戏角色必须相对容"
"易地分辨出哪个节点代表每个游戏角色ID。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:267
msgid ""
"The solution is to simply name the *root nodes of the instanced player "
"scenes as their network ID*. This way, they will be the same in every peer "
"and RPC will work great! Here is an example:"
msgstr ""
"解决方案是简单地将 **实例化后的游戏角色场景的根节点命名为它的网络ID** 。这"
"样，它们在每一个对等体中都将是相同的，并且RPC可以很好地工作！这是一个例子："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:296
msgid ""
"Depending on when you execute pre_configure_game(), you may need to change "
"any calls to ``add_child()`` to be deferred via ``call_deferred()``, as the "
"SceneTree is locked while the scene is being created (e.g. when ``_ready()`` "
"is being called)."
msgstr ""
"根据您何时执行 ``pre_configure_game()``，您可能需要将任何调用更改为 "
"``add_child()`` ，以便通过 ``call_deferred()`` 推迟，因为 ``SceneTree`` 在创"
"建场景时被锁定（例如，当 ``_ready()`` 被调用时）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:300
msgid "Synchronizing game start"
msgstr "同步游戏开始"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:302
msgid ""
"Setting up players might take different amounts of time for every peer due "
"to lag, different hardware, or other reasons. To make sure the game will "
"actually start when everyone is ready, pausing the game until all players "
"are ready can be useful:"
msgstr ""
"由于延迟、硬件不同或其他原因，为每个对等体设置游戏角色可能会花费不同的时间。"
"为了确保游戏在所有人都准备就绪时可以真正开始，请暂停游戏直到所有玩家准备就"
"绪，这很有用："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:311
msgid ""
"When the server gets the OK from all the peers, it can tell them to start, "
"as for example:"
msgstr "当服务器从所有对等体获得OK时，它才告诉他们可以开始，例如："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:332
msgid "Synchronizing the game"
msgstr "同步游戏"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:334
msgid ""
"In most games, the goal of multiplayer networking is that the game runs "
"synchronized on all the peers playing it. Besides supplying an RPC and "
"remote member variable set implementation, Godot adds the concept of network "
"masters."
msgstr ""
"在大多数游戏中，多人联网的目标是使游戏在所有玩该游戏的对等设备上同步运行。除"
"了提供RPC和远程成员变量集实现之外，Godot还添加了网络主机的概念。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:338
msgid "Network master"
msgstr "网络主机"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:340
msgid ""
"The network master of a node is the peer that has the ultimate authority "
"over it."
msgstr "一个节点的网络主机是对节点具有最终权限的对等体。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:342
msgid ""
"When not explicitly set, the network master is inherited from the parent "
"node, which if not changed, is always going to be the server (ID 1). Thus "
"the server has authority over all nodes by default."
msgstr ""
"如果未明确设置，则网络主机将从父节点继承，如果未更改，则该父节点将始终是服务"
"器（ID 1）。因此，服务器默认具有对所有节点的权限。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:344
msgid ""
"The network master can be set with the function :ref:`Node."
"set_network_master(id, recursive) <class_Node_method_set_network_master>` "
"(recursive is ``true`` by default and means the network master is "
"recursively set on all child nodes of the node as well)."
msgstr ""
"网络主机可以用函数 :ref:`Node.set_network_master(id, recursive) "
"<class_Node_method_set_network_master>` 进行设置（递归默认情况下为 ``true``，"
"这意味着也将在该节点的所有子节点上递归设置网络主机）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:347
msgid ""
"Checking that a specific node instance on a peer is the network master for "
"this node for all connected peers is done by calling :ref:`Node."
"is_network_master() <class_Node_method_is_network_master>`. This will return "
"``true`` when executed on the server and ``false`` on all client peers."
msgstr ""
"通过调用 :ref:`Node.is_network_master() "
"<class_Node_method_is_network_master>` 来检查对等体上的特定节点实例，是否是该"
"节点的所有连接对等体的网络主机。在服务器上执行时将返回 ``true``，而在所有客户"
"端对等节点上将返回 ``false``。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:349
msgid ""
"If you have paid attention to the previous example, it's possible you "
"noticed that each peer was set to have network master authority for their "
"own player (Node) instead of the server:"
msgstr ""
"如果您注意到了前面的示例，则可能已经注意到，每个对等体都被设置为对它自己的游"
"戏角色（节点）具有网络主权限，而不是服务器："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:369
msgid ""
"Each time this piece of code is executed on each peer, the peer makes itself "
"master on the node it controls, and all other nodes remain as puppets with "
"the server being their network master."
msgstr ""
"每次在每个对等体上执行这段代码时，对等体都将自己作为其控制的节点上的主机，而"
"所有其他节点都保留为傀儡，而服务器是其网络主机。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:371
msgid ""
"To clarify, here is an example of how this looks in the `bomber demo "
"<https://github.com/godotengine/godot-demo-projects/tree/master/networking/"
"multiplayer_bomber>`_:"
msgstr ""
"为了阐明，下面是一个示例，该示例看起来像在 `轰炸机演示 <https://github.com/"
"godotengine/godot-demo-projects/tree/master/networking/multiplayer_bomber>`_ "
"中一样："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:378
msgid "Master and puppet keywords"
msgstr "``master`` 和 ``puppet`` 关键字"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:382
msgid ""
"The real advantage of this model is when used with the ``master``/``puppet`` "
"keywords in GDScript (or their equivalent in C# and Visual Script). "
"Similarly to the ``remote`` keyword, functions can also be tagged with them:"
msgstr ""
"该模型的真正优势是与GDScript中的 ``master`` / ``puppet`` 关键字（或C#和"
"Visual Script中的等效关键字）一起使用。类似于 ``remote`` 关键字，函数也可以用"
"它们标记："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:385
msgid "Example bomb code:"
msgstr "炸弹代码的示例："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:393
msgid "Example player code:"
msgstr "游戏角色代码的示例："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:407
msgid ""
"In the above example, a bomb explodes somewhere (likely managed by whoever "
"is master). The bomb knows the bodies in the area, so it checks them and "
"checks that they contain an ``exploded`` function."
msgstr ""
"在上面的示例中，炸弹在某处爆炸（可能由主机控制）。炸弹知道该区域的物体，因此"
"会对它们进行检查，并检查它们是否具有一个 ``exploded`` 函数。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:410
msgid ""
"If they do, the bomb calls ``exploded`` on it. However, the ``exploded`` "
"method in the player has a ``master`` keyword. This means that only the "
"player who is master for that instance will actually get the function."
msgstr ""
"如果它们有，炸弹就会调用它们的 ``exploded`` 函数。然而，游戏角色中的 "
"``exploded`` 函数上有一个 ``master`` 关键字。这意味着，只有当游戏角色是该实例"
"的主机时, 才能实际上获得该函数。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:413
msgid ""
"This instance, then, calls the ``stun`` method in the same instances of that "
"same player (but in different peers), and only those which are set as "
"puppet, making the player look stunned in all the peers (as well as the "
"current, master one)."
msgstr ""
"然后，该实例在同一游戏角色（但在不同的对等体中）的相同实例中调用 ``stun`` 函"
"数，并且仅将那些设置为傀儡的对等体，使游戏角色在所有对等体（以及当前主机的）"
"中都看起来被击昏了。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/tutorials/networking/high_level_multiplayer.rst:416
msgid ""
"Note that you could also send the ``stun()`` message only to a specific "
"player by using ``rpc_id(<id>, \"exploded\", bomb_owner)``. This may not "
"make much sense for an area-of-effect case like the bomb, but in other "
"cases, like single target damage."
msgstr ""
"请注意，您也可以使用 ``rpc_id(<id>, \"exploded\", bomb_owner)`` 将 "
"``stun()`` 消息仅发送给一个特定游戏角色。对于像炸弹这样的有范围影响的情况，这"
"可能没有多大意义，但在其他情况下，如对单个目标的伤害，可能有意义。"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Gaffer On Games has a lot of useful articles about networking in Games "
#~ "(`here <https://gafferongames.com/tags/networking>`__), including the "
#~ "comprehensive `introduction to networking models in games <https://"
#~ "gafferongames.com/post/"
#~ "what_every_programmer_needs_to_know_about_game_networking/>`__."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Gaffer On Games上有很多关于游戏中联网的有用文章（`这里 <https://"
#~ "gafferongames.com/tags/networking>`__），包括综合型的 `游戏中的网络模型介"
#~ "绍 <https://gafferongames.com/post/"
#~ "what_every_programmer_needs_to_know_about_game_networking/>`__。"
